Package com.bookapp.bean

Class Book

java.lang.Object
com.bookapp.bean.Book
public class Book extends Object
Represents a book with details such as ID, title, author, category, and price. This class is used to encapsulate the attributes of a book and provide getter and setter methods to access and modify these attributes.

Example usage: 

 Book book = new Book(1, "Java Programming", "John Doe", "Education", 29.99);
 System.out.println(book);
Author:
MonigaBalasubramanian
